# AJAX & Security

Every AJAX entry must call `Helper::guardAjaxRequest($action)` before work (CSRF + ACL).

## Entry points

1. Admin: `Platform::handleRequests()` → `Request::initialize()`
2. Site `onAfterRoute` task switch
3. `onAjaxHelixultimate` → `HttpResponse\{Class}::{method}()`

URL shape: `option=com_ajax&helix=ultimate&action={action}`

## Must follow

- Register new actions in `Helper::getActionPermissions()` / `authorizeAction()`.
- File I/O: `Helper::sanitizeLayoutName()` + `\Joomla\Filesystem\Path::check()`.
- Media: `Helper::resolveMediaPath()` — reject `..`, stay under media root.
- Redirects: `Helper::validateInternalRedirect()` for `helixreturn`.
- Article attribs (frontend save): merge only `Helper::getHelixAttribKeys()`.
- Embeds: `Helper::sanitizeEmbed()` — never echo raw iframe HTML.
- No direct `$_POST` / `$_GET` — use `$app->input` with typed filters.

## RAW template fields

Allowlist in `Request::RAW_TEMPLATE_FIELDS` (admin-trusted HTML only):

`before_head`, `after_body`, `before_body`, `custom_css`, `custom_js`, `copyright`, `comingsoon_content`

Never use `RAW` on unauthenticated or site-public input. Add fields to both `Request.php` and the cpanel `$invalidDataFields` list when extending.

## Tests

New endpoints → add coverage under `plugins/system/helixultimate/tests/security/`.
